HEADWORD: Willowy
<hw>Wil"low*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Abounding with willows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where <qex>willowy</qex> Camus lingers with delight.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling a willow; pliant; flexible; pendent;
drooping; graceful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Willsome</ent>⟦br⟧
